        "title_top": "About Us",
        "title": "Our Mission",
        "des": "<p>Back pain affects 40% of U.S. adults, with chronic conditions impacting millions more. As our population ages, the need for precise spinal interventions has never been more critical. At DemoSpine, we meet this challenge by bridging the gap between complex anatomy and hands-on education.<br><br>\n\n\nFounded in 2024, DemoSpine is creating 3D spine models that accurately represent spinal anatomy. These models feature fully articulating and detachable S1-L2 vertebrae, allowing surgeons to demonstrate standard lumbar procedures to students and patients. Removable bone resections further enhance surgical planning and technique illustration, offering a tactile and detailed understanding of spinal procedures.<br><br>\n\nWe high-fidelity 3D models that mirror true spinal anatomy. Featuring fully articulating and detachable S1-L2 vertebrae, our models allow surgeons to demonstrate lumbar procedures with unprecedented tactile detail. By incorporating removable bone resections, we empower educators to illustrate surgical techniques with a level of realism that standard models can't match.\n\nOur mission is simple: to provide the medical community with the tools needed to improve surgical training, enhance patient communication, and ultimately drive better clinical outcomes. </p>",
